                  </hi>. I am a coach-trimmer, living at Barnet. On the 25th of December, I slept at William Robinson's, in Church-row, Ed<lb></lb>monton—I left my great coat and comforter behind the side door—I saw it soon after eleven—the next morning it was gone—(<hi rend="italic">examining the pro<lb></lb>perty</hi>)—this is my coat—I lost such a comforter and such a box.</p>
